THE IMPACT ON MY LIFE

   I instantly knew that EDHEC was for me because of its balance between
   theory and practice, its business focus and its international
   environment.EDHEC has given me concrete knowledge on how to be a
   manager in the real world, as opposed to theoretical, international
   business world.”

   Carolina Valle, Colombian, EDHEC 2014, International Product Manager,
   Juva Santé International

THE IMPACT ON MY EXPERIENCE

   The courses are extremely varied and enriching, covering family
   business governance, strategy and marketing, but also design thinking
   and leadership development. Our exchanges with our classmates are the
   cornerstone of the programme, both during classes and outside them. We
   learn from our reciprocal experiences every day."
   Hélène Savalle, 2016 GEMBA Graduate

The Impact on my employability

   One of EDHEC’s main contributions to my professional development has
   been to increase my willingness to step out of my comfort zone. This
   experience forced me to adapt quickly and helped me to become
   comfortable with new challenges"
   Alexandre Casteau (EDHEC 2015), consultant, McKinsey – Genève

THE IMPACT ON MY INTERNSHIP PREPARATION

   For me, EDHEC's strengths lie in its Career Centre, its powerful Alumni
   network and its faculty. I knew I had made the right decision by
   choosing EDHEC because from the offset we are surrounded by a support
   network whose aim is to train and help us in every possible way to
   secure positions within leading global financial institutions.
   Tania Bachmann Trostiansk, EDHEC student, Summer Analyst, Goldman Sachs
   – London

